column2: Why rely on a BMI of 24 for predicting Diabetes in a 40-year-old male with a Diabetes Pedigree Function of 0.15, rather than a BMI of 18 in a 50-year-old female with a Diabetes Pedigree Function of 0.3?
Predict(BMI = 24, Age = 40, Sex = Male, DPF = 0.15) over Predict(BMI = 18, Age = 50, Sex = Female, DPF = 0.3)
